< Review>
Visited the SmileShop in Redwood City today.   What a great experience.  The team working there were very nice and welcoming.

After filling in some personal info on their iPad, it was off to another office for the 3D image of my teeth and smile.  Quisa, a dental assistant, was efficient, friendly and fast in doing the image.  She answered all my questions.  The technology is amazing.

Once the 3D image was complete, we talked about next steps and the payment plan ($1895 or $250 down and $85 month for 24 months).  This is about the third of the cost for regular braces.  And on average, takes about 6 months of wearing aligners all the time except when eating and drinking.

I am not yet sure that I will order the aligners but I highly recommend checking out the SmileShop in Redwood City.<//Review>

When I got there I had to actually find a salesman. I was out there for like 15 min. No one came out.

The worst part was the finance guy. He was way to aggressive. Trying to sell me gap insurance.  I told him several times no. And you can tell he was frustrated with me.
Than he played the game there might be something wrong with my loan. But said it in a low tone. Than he left the room pretending to talk to his manager.
In hind sight I should of left.

They got me on a key fob fee which was bs. I should of stranded my ground but I didnt.
The other game was, he when he was trying to sell me gap insurance, it was 1600dollars. But the trick is, when you cant say you can afford it or it's too expensive they will extend the loan and pretend to bring the price down. But also he took off almost half the price of the gap insurance.
Meaning they were going to try to over sell you on gap insurance but really they can sell it for about 895.
But you can cancel the gap insurance within thirtys days which they don't tell you. And I'm going to do it.
The car salesman was cool. Your typical saleman. But he wasn't a jerk.
I should of done a better job and being more prepared.  Meaning I should of been pre approved before going there.
Lesson learned. I'll definitely be better prepared and be ready to walk away and go some where else.

I hope this will help others. If your a type of person that is kind of timid better bring someone who wont be pushed over.</Review>

<Text>I bought a 2015 Tacoma that was a trade in from this dealership about a month ago. The sales guy who sold me the car was named Jeff Ferraiuolo. As we all know, the people who seems to be the friendliest are usually the most crooked one. This was exactly that. I originally thought I got a good deal on my car but apparently I did not. As buying cars goes, Jeff and the finance guy tried to stick me with a higher apr from the start which I obviously did not agree too. After some back and forth Jeff came back and tried to use my age as a crutch to why I could not get the rate that I wanted and he went on saying due to me being a first time buyer it was not helping me. That was when I told him I was not a first time buyer and that the car parked outside was my first car purchased. He stuttered for a bit obviously due to being caught in his own lie and went back. After an hour or so we agreed on a rate. As I said before, I thought I had a good deal until I recieved a letter from Sacramento Credit Union stating that I was not approved through them during the finance process due to the amount request exceeding their policy and terms. The amount requested was over $4000 more than the price we agreed on. <user>113450317077096077101< /user><Resp>{'time': 1565624482840, 'text': "Adam, we are very sorry that your experiences haven't been positive and would welcome the ability to see what we could do for you. It's discouraging that your pizza wasn't cooked right and that you were unable to order what you requested. I've been ordering from Fresh Brothers in Hollywood for a few years now, ever since I moved into the neighborhood, and I've noticed a decline in both quality and service.

Several months ago, I ordered a cauliflower crust pizza for delivery. The delivery time was about average, however the pizza was burnt. It was late evening on the weekend, so I didn't bother to reorder.

Just today, I received an email promotion to try their newest pizza. When I tried to order online, I wasn't able to complete the transaction. When I called the shop and explained the situation, I was told that the order did not meet the minimum requirement for delivery, because the coupon code from their email special discounted the total amount to be below the minimum. I asked if they would be able to override this and allow me to order for delivery since the order did exceed the minimum requirement before the coupon, and they said no.

So, long story short, I did not order the pizza. And they did not offer up any other solution. They literally told me that the order did not meet the minimum for delivery, and that was it. With the number of other options in the Hollywood area, I will not be ordering from Fresh Brothers again, nor will I recommend them.

Fresh Brothers, I encourage you to think about your service model from a customer's perspective, and see the experience through their eyes. I also recommend that you consider adding language to both your website and your email promotions, that clearly communicates any such disclaimers.<//review>

< Review>
I'd never heard of Fresh Brothers before I moved to LA, but after living here for a while I've learned to really love their pizza. It's a great option if you are vegan, they make a great vegan cheese and vegan sausage pizza. They're regular pizza is very delicious too. They have great ingredients and the cut their pizza into squares and not a pie cut which reminds me of great pizza in Chicago. Fresh brothers is one of my favorite pizza chains now mainly because they have so many selections to choose from. It can be a little pricey but for the pizza they serve I would much rather choose fresh brothers over domino's or papa John's.</Review>

< text>
Fresh Brothers understands the meaning of customer service and quality. Let me take you to the experience I was blessed with. I strolled into Fresh Brothers on a whim of hunger. After being greeted by the front counter representative, he politely suggested options for me to try. After placing the order, it seemed that the food materialized in front of me. <Text>My friend invited my over to Fresh Brothers Pizza last night and we had a blast! There were about 10 of us and it was a great way to catch up with old friends, meet new people and eat LOTS AND LOTS OF PIZZA!

I would like to thank Debbie Goldberg for being the hostess with the mostess! She made sure that our drinks were always full and most importantly she made sure that our rather large party had plenty to eat.

Mission Accomplished!!  It has been 12 hours since I ate any food and I am still in a Pizza Coma!

So lets talk about the Fresh Brothers location itself. It is Hollywood so there is a lot of traffic and the spots in the parking lot go quickly. I rode my bike so I was able to park right in front.

This place has a lot of tv's. When I was done counting them, I found two more in the bathroom so I think the total is like 15 flatscreens for a pretty small location. I thought it was awesome! They have two tv's that point outside so you can watch tv if you are standing in front of the building.. Even more awesome!

The food was awesome. Let me take you through what I ate:

We had the fresh knots and wings. The knots were very good and they are described like this. Garlic bread tied in tasty knots, dusted with parmesan, pizza sauce on the side

After the appetizers came out, then came out the salads. I dove into the BBQ Chicken Salad  and it was very yummy. It was very fresh and here are the ingredients for that. Barbecued chicken breast over a tasty bed of romaine, cheddar cheese, corn, zesty onions and black beans topped with fried onions.

The final course was the pizzas and there was plenty to go around. To be honest, I don't know how many kinds of pizza's were out there but they were all called. My friend Dimple has a custom pizza made for her which has Sausage, Pepperoni and Red Onions on it. I think I might have liked it the best. I hope to see the Dimple Special on the menu sometime soon..

The Bottom Line: The food here is awesome and they have 10 locations throughout Los Angeles. I would recommend trying any of them!</Text><user_name>Bower Louber< /user_name>< GmapID>

<time>1443212290766</time>< Rating>
2< /Rating>
< Text>
He was polite and fast. Area of work was a bit sketchy but clean. Relatively cheap at $130 however you get what you pay for.

Now for the bad portion of the review;

The online photo was not accurate to what the area actually looks like. Advertised nice suite at a shopping center and ended up a garage behind a shop on union ave.
Clean but hard to get to.
The work it self as far as the cut and stick was good, however the problem was the dirt from the windows wasn't properly cleaned and the film attained copious amounts of dust from the window because of it. The door window panels weren't removed to lengthen the film to insure no peeling. End result was relatively good work ruined by lazy work ethic on cleaning dust off windows before applying product. and not properly installing door windows.

Recommendations:

1)Clean windows!
2) Take protecting layer off inside the car not outside to avoid dust collection.
3) if your going to measure using outside window to measure, properly clean that too before touching film to it.
4) if you want word to spread about your business you need to supply good business to bring back costumers for repeat business and to tell others. Good luck in your endeavors. As for this costumer I won't be returning.</Text>

< Review>
Today is September 26, 2015 and I just got my windows tinted by Alex here at Hills Window Tinting and they turned out AMAZING! Who would have thought that window tinting can look so good haha! Its right across the street from the kern county fairgrounds and the price is AMAZING compared to all other shops. This was the most affordable that I found in town and I am not dissapointed. The outside is a little rough around the edges especially since its across the street from the fairgrounds, but DONT LET THAT FOOL YOU! To be honest I was a little iffy because the price was almost to good to be true for great quality work and the outside appearance made me wanna go to a big name shop to get it done, but I am SOOOO glad I didnt haha! I have learned not judge a book by its cover. Alex is the perfect combination of business and friendly. He is so nice and explains everything in detail. Great customer service and gets it done in half the time of other shops that I have called for a fraction of the cost (depending on what you want) still affordable and WORTH IT! Highly recommend to others! You wont be disappointed I promise!</Review>

<Name>Gwen Morrison< /Name><Review>We were very underwhelmed by our dinner here. They charge high prices for mediocre Italian food.
To start, we had a hard little loaf of uncut, cold, stale bread brought to us. The waitress never brought any more to us. There's a big bottle of cheap olive oil on every table. The crust on the bread was like a rock.
We had the brussel sprouts as an appetizer because they did not have our first THREE choices of appetizer- said they were all out. The brussel sprouts were quite good, actually.
For entrees, my husband got the Mahi Mahi. He was disappointed. The fish itself was NOT fresh at all, and the pesto was very lacking in flavor, and had way too much cheese. Overall a very bland dish that he didnt want to finish. I had the Butternut Tortellacci with tomato soup, which was a decent meal, but not terribly impressive. The soup was very bland.
We decided not to even try dessert.
The only reason this is three stars instead of two is that the service was very fast.
Number one thing to improve: hire someone who knows how to bake bread, and make it FRESH.< /Review>< GmapID>

< Review>
This review is for a Grubhub delivery.

The food was good and packaged well aside from the oil and vinegar cups for the bread having opened and spilled inside the bag.

I ordered the signature truffle Mac and cheese and crispy mozzarella bites. The crispy mozz bites seemed like they had been way overcooked as they were all hemorrhaging dry, fried mozzarella and the insides were hollow.

My biggest problem however was ordering pasta from a restaurant whose menu consists primarily of pasta dishes, and not getting ANY silverware or napkins. How was this missed?? I had to call down to the front desk of my hotel and have someone bring a fork because no one at Romano's threw one in, and the Grubhub drivers don't stick around long enough to verify an order with the customer.

I disagree with the fundamental trend of sacrificing service for convenience and with a Grubhub delivery, I'm noticing no one takes accountability for an order. Sure, I can call the restaurant, but do I want to wait another 30 minutes for someone to drive back out to make my order right? This is compounded by the fact that my tip is pre-emptively applied so my one method of rewarding good service or highlighting bad is taken away from me.

I think both the restaurant and GH could do better. The restaurant needs to take better care with remote orders and ensure they are all 100% before going out the door, since problem resolution is much more complicated and time consuming; and I think GH as a service provider needs to emphasize *correct* service over *fast* service and incentivize workers at all points in the chain to follow suit.

I'm upset at RMG for not knowing their business and failing to include silverware to a hotel order for a food that *cannot* be eaten with hands, and GH needs to ensure orders that go through their process are correct before eating a customer's time and money. Next time I need to eat, I'll just go sit down at the restaurant. At least then when there's a problem, I can settle it immediately.< /Review>

<rate>3</rate>< Text>
Party of six celebrating a birthday.
Service was attentive.
Large white sheets of paper covered the tables,  crayons provided for the young at heart.
For a Wednesday night, it was not crowded at dinner time, approximately 6 p.m.
3 of us had the chicken marsala. 1 had spaghetti and meatballs, shrimp scampi, and another had pasta alfredo.
The food was good, but not great in my humble opinion.
My chicken marsala was good but lacked the depth the marsala sauce typically carries.
The others in our party did seem pleased with their dish though.
Warm bread was served along with dipping sauce of spices and herbs in olive oil and balsamic vinegar may also be added.
It was very good.
The ladies room could be a bit more clean, and parking lot had a lot more cars than patrons.
We thought the place was packed judging by the cars in the lot near the entrance into the restaurant,  but only a couple of seated patrons.
Choice of chocolate cake or baked cheesecake with sliced strawberries on the side for the birthday girl.
I will most likely return to try another dish sometime in the future.< /Text>

< Review>
When my wife and I were first married, we used to save so we could go to one of our favorite places-Romano's Macaroni Grill! Then we moved away from any locations and have missed it.  Traveling through the area today, we were excited to see a RMG! We saw the reviews, but thought that surely they must be mistaken, this is Romano's after all...right?  Here's our experience.  The greeter was very friendly and courteous to us throughout the visit.  He greeted us warmly when we entered, came and chatted briefly with us while we were waiting for our food, and opened the door for us when we left.  The server was alright as well.  But, that's where the positives ended.  Granted, I am comparing things with a memory, but if this is indicative of current practices, things have definitely changed.  The oil and basalmic poured out with the appetizer bread that used to be served have been replaced by some oil and pepper.  The small loaf was cold and hard.  My shoes stuck to the floor around our table.  The restroom was dirty and in need of repair.  Gone was the music piped into the restaurant and the atmosphere that was created there in the past.  When the food arrived, I thought the chicken I ate was off for some reason.  After a couple of bites I realized what it was.  It tasted exactly like the chicken that is reconstituted after being frozen in a microwave dinner.  I didn't eat any more of it.  The pasta was well cooked, but the sauces were lacking.  To cap it off, a family member who has the chicken parmesan came home with a very upset stomach.  I still don't want to give up on RMG, with so many GOOD memories from the past.  But I'm left with the impression that I should leave my experiences with RMG at that, the good memories.  Disappointing to say the least.<//Review>

<Review>The food was very good, and the portions extremely generous; you'll definitely have leftovers, which makes the slightly high prices worth it. The waitstaff was pleasant and the service was fast - we got our salads about five minutes after we placed our orders, and the entr√©es arrived before I had even finished my salad. This place also serves fresh baked bread (focaccia) for the table, which was nice and hot. I ordered the classic truffle mac and cheese, which was a little bit spicy (comes with black pepper in it) and very cheesy, but a little drier than I was hoping it would be (I like my mac and cheese very creamy). Overall, this is a nice place that I would visit a few times a year because of the prices and how heavy the food is.</Review>< pics>

<review>EDIT (Jun/2018): This place is decaying fast. It appears their corporate overlords decided that they only want your money and don't care for your experience. On our last visit, we had to wait 40+ minutes to sit, even though the place was about 1/4 full. Empty tables everywhere and no servers to take customers. To me, this indicates a company that wants to keep costs low by employing fewer server than they need. After our wait, we were served by a very disinterested waiter. The free bread (one of the selling points of the place) is still there, but was clearly not fresh as it used to be. They now charge extra for salads and soup. In the end, we spent around 3h+ to have a very dissatisfying experience. I won't be coming back anytime soon. It's a real shame, since the place used to be a good place to eat casually.

OLD REVIEW:
Good "bang for the buck". It's not "authentic" Italian food, but the taste is good. Not super expensive and the setting is very nice for what you pay for. A nice loaf of bread is included as an appetizer when you order any entree.</review>< Pics>

<Pics>None<//Pics><GmapID>0x808fc8df6b0d67af:0x9d419fde15e00c1f</GmapID>< review>
I'm NEVER one to complain, but my experience here on 10/7/18 warrants it!!

It was an absolute disaster from the beginning. When we got first got there, we were told that there was approx. 25 min wait for a party of 4... no big thing...

After my personal observation, I noticed that there were several open tables where the recent parties just departed. These tables sat open for 15 mins or more, and then I realized that who ever did the scheduling did not have enough bussers available. I only saw a bus boy cleaning tables.  TALK ABOUT BEING GROSSLY UNDERSTAFFED! C'MON MAN!

After inquiring with the host/manager after 35 mins, we were then seated. The table wasnt prepared, no utensil settings, no glasses... really?!? Being patient, I let it slide...

Waiter eventually came around and took our order after sitting arnd for 10 mins. Again, no utensil settings but we got our drinks... and bread...  but no utensils. I finally had to ask another waiter if we could get some settings...

We placed 3 orders of appetizers; calamari, mac n cheese bites, and fresh mozzarella. Calamari came w/in 10 mins of the initial order. We proceeded to order our main dishes.

Our main dish came in 35 mins w/in ordering it, but the other appetizers havent arrived yet and no explanation... wth?!  After working into our main dish, the remaining appetizers came 42 mins since placing it and 7 mins AFTER the main dish arrived.

After waiting all that time, we really didnt have any appetite to eat any more... would you or any one??? C'MON MAN!

Where is John Taffer when you need him? Good grief, talk about a bootleg operation! C'MON MAN!

If you have time to burn and really dont care about the quality of service, then this is your place. Sadly, for the price that they demand, you're better off cooking the meal yourself without the unwanted stress!!

In my personal observation, this place lacks:
* communication
* integrity
* compassion
* desire

Sadly, we were among 5 other parties who were waiting for service in this bootleg operation. John Taffer would scream out, "you're in the customer service business and your livelihood depends on it!! Are you f$&n crazy?!?"

Needless to say, our party left extremely disappointed. If I was a representative from this corporation and experienced what I went through, there would be a lot of unemployed people with the fear of this place shutting down..

This place is broken and needs help! Sorry to be brutally honest, but I'm pulling for you guys to stay in business...< /review>

<user_id>106951408214813421843< /user_id><Name>Benjamin Lopez</Name><date>1537369622255<//date><rating>2</rating>< text>
I came for lunch as a small company event for 5 people and the service was sub par.  We were seated promptly on a busy afternoon lunch. The things I want to highlight are that we did not have bread offered to our table.  I ended up requesting the bread which did not arrive until after our appetizers were eaten.  Another issue was that once the bread arrived, our table did not have the black oil condoment. Another issue is that our waitor was reaching across peoples faces while delivering and retrieving plates.  Lastly, I ordered medium cooked lamb chops and two of the three peices of meet were good. Unfortunately the third piece was burned on one side.  The meat was so charred when I bit into it, it tasted like coal.

Asthetically, the area looked over crowded and simply not the best.  The environment may need reevaluation.  On this note, I was not impressed by a paper cover over the table mantles.

I can safely say that this site is understaffed.  We were waited on by 4 different waiters.  I can chalk up the reaching for plates across people as rushing through the task. As for the  burnt food, it's not easy to serve so many at a busy time.  Or maybe training is required for waiters and cooks to emphasize quality of service.

All of this is unfortunate but I wanted to give pinpointed feedback to the site.< /text>
